<item>
            <title>[SOLR-603] Support Partial Optimizes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-603</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It would be useful if Solr supported Lucene&apos;s capability to do partial optimizes.  The associated method on the IndexWriter is &lt;a href=&quot;http://lucene.apache.org/java/2_3_2/api/core/org/apache/lucene/index/IndexWriter.html#optimize(int,%20boolean)&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://lucene.apache.org/java/2_3_2/api/core/org/apache/lucene/index/IndexWriter.html#optimize(int,%20boolean)&lt;/a&gt; and the variations there-in.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
