                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12606882" author="gsingers" created="Fri, 20 Jun 2008 21:15:47 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Adds capability to do &amp;lt;optimize maxOptimizeSegments=&quot;5&quot;/&amp;gt; which means that one can specify the maximum number of segments to leave when doing optimize.  This is useful for controlling how long optimizes take.  Adds test in DirectUpdateHandlerOptimizeTest.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also deprecates the DirectUpdateHandler.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12606888" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Fri, 20 Jun 2008 21:43:55 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;nit: maxOptimizeSegments seems a bit wordy... how about numSegments or maxSegments?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12607239" author="gsingers" created="Mon, 23 Jun 2008 15:11:27 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Adds SolrJ support.  Make the parameter a bit smaller (maxSegments instead of maxOptimizeSegments)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Will commit in a day or two&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
